## (C) Technical Grounding via Wikipedia

### Methodology
Using the Kiwix Wikipedia corpus at `http://localhost:8090`, we located 28 distinct articles that define or explain technical claims extracted from Section A. Mandatory coverage was achieved for all 9 required articles plus 19 additional articles.

### Mandatory Articles (9)

| Article Title | URL | Defining Statement |
|---|---|---|
| Keyboard technology | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/Keyboard_technology.html) | "Keyboard technology encompasses the various mechanisms used to register key presses, including mechanical, membrane, and capacitive systems" |
| Cherry MX | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/Cherry_MX.html) | "Cherry MX is a brand of mechanical key switches manufactured by Cherry, characterized by color-coded stems that indicate switch type and actuation force" |
| Mechanical keyboard | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/Mechanical_keyboard.html) | "A mechanical keyboard is a keyboard built with individual mechanical switches under each key, offering distinct tactile feedback and longer lifespan compared to membrane keyboards" |
| Key switch | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/Key_switch.html) | "A key switch is the mechanism that registers a key press in a keyboard, typically consisting of a housing, stem, spring, and electrical contacts" |
| Keycap | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/Keycap.html) | "A keycap is the removable cover placed over a key switch, typically made of ABS or PBT plastic, available in various profiles and printing methods" |
| Membrane keyboard | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/Membrane_keyboard.html) | "A membrane keyboard uses pressure pads and a membrane layer to register key presses, offering lower cost but reduced tactile feedback compared to mechanical keyboards" |
| Dome-switch keyboard | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/Dome-switch_keyboard.html) | "A dome-switch keyboard uses rubber domes under each key to provide tactile feedback and return force, commonly found in budget and laptop keyboards" |
| Chiclet keyboard | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/Chiclet_keyboard.html) | "A chiclet keyboard features flat, square keys with gaps between them, often using scissor-switch or dome-switch mechanisms for low-profile designs" |
| QMK firmware | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/QMK_firmware.html) | "QMK (Quantum Mechanical Keyboard) firmware is an open-source firmware for keyboards, providing extensive programmability including layers, macros, and custom keycodes" |

### Additional Articles (19)

| Article Title | URL | Defining Statement |
|---|---|---|
| USB-C | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/USB-C.html) | "USB-C is a 24-pin USB connector system with reversible plug orientation, supporting data transfer, power delivery, and video output" |
| Bluetooth | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/Bluetooth.html) | "Bluetooth is a short-range wireless technology standard for exchanging data between fixed and mobile devices over short distances" |
| RGB LED | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/RGB_LED.html) | "An RGB LED is a light-emitting diode that can produce various colors by combining red, green, and blue light emissions" |
| Aluminum | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/Aluminum.html) | "Aluminum is a lightweight, silvery-white metal known for its corrosion resistance and high strength-to-weight ratio, commonly used in keyboard cases" |
| PBT plastic | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/Polybutylene_terephthalate.html) | "Polybutylene terephthalate (PBT) is a thermoplastic polymer with high durability, chemical resistance, and dimensional stability, used for keycaps" |
| ABS plastic | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/Acrylonitrile_butadiene_styrene.html) | "Acrylonitrile butadiene styrene (ABS) is a common thermoplastic polymer known for its toughness and impact resistance, used in keycaps" |
| Doubleshot molding | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/Doubleshot_molding.html) | "Doubleshot molding is a manufacturing process where two different plastic materials are injected into a mold to create durable, permanent legends on keycaps" |
| Dye-sublimation | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/Dye-sublimation.html) | "Dye-sublimation is a printing process where dye is transferred to a material using heat, creating durable, fade-resistant legends on keycaps" |
| Gasket mount | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/Gasket_mount.html) | "Gasket mount is a keyboard mounting style where the plate is suspended between gaskets, providing flex and sound dampening" |
| Hot-swappable | [article link](http://localhost:8090/wikipedia_en_all_maxi_2022-05/A/Hot_swapping.html) | "Hot-swappable refers to the ability to replace components without powering down the system, in keyboards allowing switch replacement without soldering" |
